title: Barbie film tops $1bn in box office sales
description: Barbie might be synonymous with pink - but her film is now firmly in the green, with more than $1bn (£784m) in box office sales worldwide.

title: Bus crash in Morocco kills at least 24 people
description: At least 24 people have died after a bus overturned in central Morocco, one of the deadliest such accidents in recent years in the country.

title: Dramatic video shows people being rescued in the Mediterranean - as mother and child die in shipwreck
description: Dramatic footage shows people being rescued from choppy seas in the Mediterranean - as reports emerge that a mother and her one-year-old child have lost their lives after two boats capsized.

title: Niger coup: Deadline arrives for leaders to stand down and reinstate president
description: A deadline for Niger's coup leaders to stand down and reinstate the country's elected president has arrived.

title: Former Pakistan PM Imran Khan spends night in high-security prison after arrest
description: Pakistan's former prime minister Imran Khan has spent the night in a high-security prison after he was handed a three-year jail term for illegally selling state gifts.

title: Kim Jong Un tells arms factories to increase production - days after Russia's defence minister visits
description: North Korean arms factories have been told to increase their output by leader Kim Jong Un, as part of a drive to upgrade the country's defence capabilities, state media reports.

title: At least 15 people killed and more than 50 injured after train derails in Pakistan
description: At least 15 people have been killed and more than 50 are injured after a train derailed in Pakistan.

title: Seen a TikTok trend about castor oil? Why rubbing it in your eyes is a bad idea
description: Doctors have issued a warning not to use castor oil as a way to treat vision problems following claims on TikTok.

title: Blood transfusion centre in Ukraine hit by Russian bomb, Zelenskyy says
description: A Russian bomb has hit a blood transfusion centre in the Ukrainian region of Kharkiv, Volodymyr Zelenskyy has claimed.
